    Class Description
    ArraySpectrum
    An implementation of the spectrum back by an array.
    ArraySpectrumComparator  
    ArrayTheoreticalSpectrum
    An array based implementation of the theoretical spectrum allow faster process
    DatabaseIndexer
    A simple database indexer for protein sequences.
    DecoySeqGenerator
    Generate decoy sequences from fasta database by reversing the sequence
    IonTypeMapper
    Generate a mapping between ion type and an index this index is used to represent ion type in array theoretical spectrum
    MixDB  
    MixDBSearcher
    This class is the main entry point into mixdb tool, it setup input parameters from command line perform different type of searches depending on input and generates outputs.
    MixIonType
    Represent mix ion type
    MixTheoSpectrumFactory
    Theoretical spectrum factory for creating mixture spectrum under the framework of TheoreticalSpectrumFactory (see that class for detail)
    MixturePeptideType
    Represent co-eluting peptides in mixture spectra, distinguish high-abundance peptides and low abundance peptide
    MixtureScorerAdapter
    Please see TheoreticalSpectrumFactory for the basic framework of theoretical spectrum.
    MixtureSVMClassify
    Perform SVM classification for mixture spectrum using svm_light
    MixtureTDA
    Perform SVM classification of
    RankBaseScoreAdapter
    Convert old scoring function to new one (see TheoreticalSpectrumFactrory) This adaptor provide methods that covert scoring models in the old framework to the new one.
    SimpleDBSearcher
    An implementation of the DBSearcher interface that aim at searching single-peptide per query spectrum (as oppotion to MixDBSearcher which search multi-peptide matches to a query spectrum).
    SimpleIonType
    Represent the ion type generated from a single peptides
    SimplePeptideType
    A simple peptide type
    SortedSpectrumReader
    Read a spectrum file in increasing parentmass manner
    SuffArrayTest  
    TheoreticalSpectrumFactory
    Factory to create theoretcial spectrum from single peptide In order to allow fast analyzing and processing spectrum, we redesign the framework used to deal with theoretical spectrum.
    TheoSpectrumGenerator
    A class that takes in a peptide database, it generate theoretical spectrum for the peptides candidates, to be efficient it store a subsset of the theoretical spectrum in memory, so it won't need to re-create the theo-spectrum repeatedly
    TheoSpectrumIndexer
    implements the database interface, represent a collection of theoretical spectrum
